body: Would having a method to build the correct identifier object be preferrable? Something like `$query->newIdentifier('max_value')` or `$query->newExpr()->newIdentifier('max_value')` work?
@markstory that's a great idea. Maybe just call it `identifier(..)`
I'm wondering what the actual intention is to hide expression package classes? I'm using them a lot, mostly `IdentifierExpression`, `TupleComparison`, and `FieldTrait`/`FieldInterface`.

@ndm Internal classes have no backwards compatibility promised on them. We use them as a way to limit the scope of the 'public' API we offer, and to reserve the right to change potentially unstable features.

issue.title: Adds Query::identifier() method

issue.body:
closes #10085 

Adds a new query method that resolves the problem of having to use an internal class `IdentifierExpression` in queries.
